body:
When using a fork (`Mainnet Fork`, `Sepolia Fork`...), the block number appears to start at zero and not at the actual block the chain was forked at. After deploying the following contract on a fork, calling the function `foo` with, for example, `nb==10` will revert.

```Solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED
pragma solidity 0.8.18;

contract Test {

    function foo(uint256 nb) external returns (bytes32){
        return blockhash(block.number-nb);
    }
}
```

